Prunes in Port

This is an excellent relish with most any poultry or game dish and is simple to make. Merely choose large tender dried prunes and soak them in port for several days in a covered jar or crock. Serve them as they are or pit them and stuff with nuts or brandied fruits.

They will keep for months this way.
